collections.name: ChronoMuse
collections.description:
ChronoMuse is not just digital art, it is a ritual of unity with nature. Each work was created at the moment when I was physically and emotionally immersed in the season of the year: inhaling the smell of winter frost, listening to spring rain, feeling the summer heat on my skin, collecting autumn leaves. A person who purchases this NFT becomes a keeper of not only art, but also the energy of this moment - fragile, like the first snow, or bright, like a fire flame. Immersing yourself in this state with me, through digital art. 
"Seasons change. Femininity is eternal."

collections.name: LonelyPixelArt
collections.description: A melancholic pixel art scene that captures the beauty of solitude. A lone figure sits on a bench under a dimly lit streetlamp, gazing at the endless night sky filled with stars. The soft glow of the light and the gentle breeze swaying the trees create a nostalgic and dreamy atmosphere. This artwork evokes a sense of longing, peace, and quiet reflection—perfect for those who find beauty in solitude.

collections.name: Restless Souls
collections.description:
Restless Souls is an NFT collection that captures the raw and rebellious spirit of 90s grunge and underground rock. Inspired by torn gig posters, iconic album covers, and the visceral energy of counterculture, each piece represents the restless souls who live for sound and freedom.

With artworks ranging from distressed xerox textures to glitch aesthetics, every NFT is a visual tribute to the golden era of alternative rock.

🎸 Collection Highlights:

Grunge, punk, and vintage-inspired designs with rough textures and an underground aesthetic.
Rare NFTs include exclusive sound elements and hidden musical easter eggs.
Created for true music lovers, collectors, and digital art enthusiasts.
⚡ Join the movement. Own your NFT and let your restless soul echo through eternity.

collections.name: Armored Cruiser - Gif
collections.description: Armored cruiser launched on water in 1898 and handed over to Great Britain after the war, which scrapped her in 1922. The ship had 2 cannons caliber 240mm, 8 cannons caliber 150mm, 18 cannons caliber 47mm guns and 2 torpedo tubes. During the war, the ship blockaded the coast of Montenegro. The ship's crew participated in the rebellion in Boka Kotorska, and towards the end of the war, the ship served as a command and accommodation facility in Šibenik.
